race.comment: NEVERMIND (4) was in the minors when resuming at this track where he finished third (23.12) in a Grade 5. Sure to be fitter. Expected to feature in the finish again. RYDER'S MAGIC (5) was unfavoured last start but led all the way to score by a nose (22.65) at Ballarat in a Grade 5 over 390m. Shapes as a top winning chance on latest effort. CANDY STRIDE (1) tends to take a while to wind up, running on to score two back before spotting a start latest and finishing on strongly into third (24.11) in a Grade 5 at Bendigo. The form from her last run stacks up well. Hard to beat again. CROCODILE ROLL (2) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.
